name: CancelSchedule
documentation:
Command to cancel a previously scheduled message using its {@link #scheduleId}.

This command instructs Fluxzero to remove a scheduled message if it hasn't yet been delivered. Cancellation is idempotent â€” if the schedule does not exist, the command has no effect.

@see io.fluxzero.common.api.scheduling.Schedule @see io.fluxzero.common.api.scheduling.SerializedSchedule

fields.name: guarantee
fields.documentation: Delivery guarantee for the cancellation action.

fields.name: scheduleId
fields.documentation: The ID of the scheduled message to be cancelled.

methods.name: routingKey
methods.documentation: Returns the routing key used for this command. Equals the {@code scheduleId}.
